 Singer Tekno has apologised to Lagosians and the general public after videos of semi-nude women dancing in a transparent truck went viral. The singer and producer said they were shooting a music video and there was shortage of vehicles when they had to move locations. The action is said to be against the Criminal Law of Lagos, Section 136 2015 which states that any person who commits any act of gross indecency with another person in public commits an offence and liable to a conviction to three years imprisonment. And Section 134(a) of the same law states that any indecent act in a public place makes both parties engaging in the act liable to imprisonment for two years. Tekno’s heartfelt apology was posted on his Instagram page. See below:  The post Tekno apologises over #Trending Video of Semi-Nude Women Dancing in Transparent Truck appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija Tekno is the tope news on everyone’s feed after he was unveiled with four others as the personalities behind the display of semi-nude women dancing seductively in a display truck in traffic around the Lekki-Ikoyi link bridge in Lagos. The video surfaced online on Friday and has  caused an uproar on… August 4, 2019 In "Entertainment" Popular musician, Augustine Kelechi, otherwise known as Tekno, as well as four others risk being jailed for two years for publicly shooting a music video depicting semi-Nood women dancing seductively in a display truck in traffic around the Lekki-Ikoyi link bridge in Lagos. Tekno was seen dancing with the semi-clad… August 4, 2019 In "Wedding Digest" The Lagos State Signage & Advertisement Agency (LASAA) has reacted to a viral video on social media wherein music star, Tekno is seen with semi-nude women dancing in an outdoor mobile advertising truck. The footage was captured around the Lekki/Ikoyi Toll Gate at the weekend. Mobolaji Sanusi, LASAA Managing Director,… August 4, 2019 In "News"